WEBVTT

00:04.352 --> 00:07.050
<i>[slow music]</i>

00:07.094 --> 00:14.231
<i>♪</i>

00:20.716 --> 00:22.631
- I don't wanna go
to work today.

00:22.674 --> 00:24.720
- Just tell the bad guys
to take a week off.

00:24.763 --> 00:27.244
- Mm, I like this plan.

00:27.288 --> 00:29.377
<i>[phone buzzes]</i>

00:29.420 --> 00:32.728
- Mm.
Don't get it.

00:32.771 --> 00:34.773
<i>[phone buzzes]</i>

00:34.817 --> 00:37.124
Mm-mm.
- Mm!

00:37.167 --> 00:39.604
I have to.
- Ugh.

00:39.648 --> 00:40.649
[groans]
No.

00:40.692 --> 00:41.737
- Dude, I have to.
- Don't do it.

00:41.780 --> 00:44.566
Don't do it!
- [laughs] I have to.

00:44.609 --> 00:50.920
<i>♪</i>

00:50.963 --> 00:53.053
- What's up?

00:53.096 --> 00:55.403
- Looks like my dad collapsed.

00:55.446 --> 00:57.405
He had a heart attack.
He's at Med right now.

00:57.448 --> 00:58.754
- What?

00:58.797 --> 01:00.234
Is this out of the blue?
Is he not feeling well?

01:00.277 --> 01:03.063
- Uh, no--I don't really talk
to him anymore, but...

01:03.106 --> 01:05.239
my mom said he's doing better.

01:05.282 --> 01:07.197
I don't know, not drinking,
exercising,

01:07.241 --> 01:09.417
you know, "changed."
Whatever.

01:09.460 --> 01:10.548
- Let's go.
I'll take you to Med.

01:10.592 --> 01:12.072
- Okay.

01:12.115 --> 01:17.207
<i>♪</i>

01:17.251 --> 01:18.339
- I'll let you out
when we get there,

01:18.382 --> 01:19.557
and I'll look for parking.

01:19.601 --> 01:20.906
- That's okay.
You don't have to come in.

01:20.950 --> 01:22.386
- You sure?

01:22.430 --> 01:24.084
- Yeah.
Thank you.

01:24.127 --> 01:25.476
<i>- Units on the city-wide.</i>

01:25.520 --> 01:26.912
<i>We got a call of a man
down in an alley,</i>

01:26.956 --> 01:29.698
<i>possible homicide.
4220 West Maypole.</i>

01:29.741 --> 01:31.961
- That's five blocks away.
Come on, let's roll.

01:32.004 --> 01:34.224
- Roll?
What about your dad?

01:34.268 --> 01:36.270
- I'll go later.

01:36.313 --> 01:39.316
5021 Henry, plainclothes
officers responding.

01:39.360 --> 01:42.276
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:42.319 --> 01:43.581
<i>♪</i>

01:43.625 --> 01:45.844
- Halstead and Upton,
intelligence.

01:45.888 --> 01:47.716
- What do we have, officer?
- Homeless guy found him.

01:47.759 --> 01:49.892
Notified a store owner
who called 911.

01:55.158 --> 01:57.682
- Two gunshot wounds
to the back.

01:57.726 --> 01:58.640
- What is this?

01:58.683 --> 02:01.425
- He's ice cold.

02:01.469 --> 02:03.601
- Oh, man, he's a cop.

02:03.645 --> 02:10.565
<i>♪</i>

02:21.097 --> 02:23.578
Patrol Officer Mike Blaine.
He's got 22 years on the job--

02:23.621 --> 02:26.581
- You gotta be kidding me.
- What?

02:26.624 --> 02:28.626
- Man, I knew him.
- Oh.

02:28.670 --> 02:30.498
- We worked together
four years in Vice.

02:30.541 --> 02:33.457
Like, I knew him well.
- I'm so sorry, Sarge.

02:33.501 --> 02:36.156
- All right, what else?
- Two shots in the back.

02:36.199 --> 02:38.158
We found
two .45 caliber casings

02:38.201 --> 02:39.811
about ten feet
from the body.

02:39.855 --> 02:42.249
- Time of death?
- Around 11:00 p.m. last night.

02:44.599 --> 02:46.731
- Robbery?
- Don't think so.

02:46.775 --> 02:49.386
Watch, wallet, cash--
all found on him.

02:49.430 --> 02:51.649
- There's no sign
of a struggle, either.

02:51.693 --> 02:53.608
- Sounds like an ambush.
- Yeah.

02:53.651 --> 02:54.957
- We know what he was
doing over here?

02:55.000 --> 02:56.219
- No, sir.

02:56.263 --> 02:57.220
Doesn't sound like
he was on the clock.

02:57.264 --> 02:58.917
- You telling me
he wasn't on OT?

02:58.961 --> 03:02.225
- His sergeant said he turned
in his squad keys at 10:00 p.m.

03:02.269 --> 03:03.792
- Checked his car.

03:03.835 --> 03:06.360
Saber radio, duty rig,
vest--all packed.

03:06.403 --> 03:08.710
Everything indicates
he was done with his tour.

03:08.753 --> 03:10.842
- Right, I don't have to
tell you there's gonna be a lot

03:10.886 --> 03:13.497
of eyes on this, so we do it
by the numbers, understand?

03:13.541 --> 03:16.413
PODs, cameras, witnesses.
Let's go.

03:20.243 --> 03:24.769
- I'll see you
on the other side, Mike.

03:24.813 --> 03:26.641
- Any word on your dad?
- Uh, yeah.

03:26.684 --> 03:28.512
Doctors confirmed
it was a heart attack.

03:28.556 --> 03:30.297
But he's in
stable condition, so...

03:30.340 --> 03:31.950
- If you gotta take off,
I totally get it.

03:31.994 --> 03:33.387
- Nah, they're doing tests.

03:33.430 --> 03:35.084
Can't do anything for him,
anyway.

03:35.127 --> 03:36.738
- Okay--I mean, are you sure?

03:36.781 --> 03:38.696
It might be nice
to just go see him.

03:38.740 --> 03:41.569
A cop just got shot.
Let's focus on that, 'kay?

03:41.612 --> 03:44.528
- All right.
- Sergeant!

03:44.572 --> 03:47.183
- Look, he's my partner.
- Hey, it's okay!

03:47.227 --> 03:50.839
Let him through.

03:50.882 --> 03:53.102
- Had to see it
with my own eyes.

03:53.145 --> 03:55.844
Rodriguez.
- Hank Voight.

03:55.887 --> 03:58.020
- You're Sergeant Voight?
- Uh-huh.

03:58.063 --> 04:00.631
- Mike spoke highly of you.
I'm glad you're on this.

04:00.675 --> 04:03.286
- Listen, you guys got anything
on the books over here?

04:03.330 --> 04:05.854
- No, sir.
Been working a burglary detail.

04:05.897 --> 04:07.551
Gold Coast, all year.

04:07.595 --> 04:09.553
- I assume everything's good
with Dana, right?

04:09.597 --> 04:13.775
- Yeah, happily married.
18 years.

04:13.818 --> 04:15.429
- Listen, man,
this is a rough neighborhood.

04:15.472 --> 04:17.648
You got any idea why Mike
would be over here?

04:17.692 --> 04:19.084
- No.

04:19.128 --> 04:21.130
Shift ended, said he was
going straight home to Dana.

04:21.173 --> 04:23.306
Said she made lasagna.

04:23.350 --> 04:26.483
- Anything unusual
the past few weeks?

04:26.527 --> 04:28.093
- Not really.

04:28.137 --> 04:30.400
The only thing I can think of
is, he went off-book

04:30.444 --> 04:31.923
two days ago
for a couple of hours.

04:31.967 --> 04:33.098
- 'Kay.

04:33.142 --> 04:34.448
- Said he had
a doctor's appointment.

04:34.491 --> 04:36.624
Didn't ring true.

04:36.667 --> 04:38.103
- Tom?

04:38.147 --> 04:40.105
- [sighs]

04:40.149 --> 04:41.455
There's Dana.

04:41.498 --> 04:43.195
Look, I have to go--
- No, no.

04:43.239 --> 04:44.545
Let me talk to her.

04:44.588 --> 04:47.374
Here, just remember
it's an active crime scene.

04:47.417 --> 04:49.376
- Thanks, Sarge.
- Dana...

04:49.419 --> 04:51.116
- Hank...

04:51.160 --> 04:52.857
- I'm sorry, ma'am.

04:52.901 --> 04:56.470
- I'm so sorry.

04:56.513 --> 05:00.822
<i>♪</i>

05:00.865 --> 05:02.389
- Sarge.

05:02.432 --> 05:05.827
So techs found faint tire
impressions near Blaine's body.

05:05.870 --> 05:08.308
It all points
to a small model vehicle.

05:08.351 --> 05:09.787
Corroborates what
a witness saw,

05:09.831 --> 05:12.094
a compact vehicle
speeding away with...

05:12.137 --> 05:14.444
lightning bolts for taillights.

05:14.488 --> 05:18.187
That adds up
to a 2017-to-19 Prius model.

05:18.230 --> 05:20.755
Problem is,
no Priuses are registered

05:20.798 --> 05:23.366
to anyone in the area.
- Okay, keep chasing it.

05:23.410 --> 05:25.499
- Yes...

05:30.330 --> 05:31.679
- What?

05:34.682 --> 05:36.727
- We also got
some suspicious texts

05:36.771 --> 05:38.163
from Blaine's phone
to a burner phone

05:38.207 --> 05:39.382
a couple days ago.

05:39.426 --> 05:41.036
Blaine says, "You got it?"

05:41.079 --> 05:42.646
Five minutes later,
he gets a text back--

05:42.690 --> 05:44.648
"Wilson Park, 2:00 p.m."

05:44.692 --> 05:48.043
- So we pulled security footage
from the park,

05:48.086 --> 05:51.655
and, uh, we got Blaine here
walking at 2:05 p.m., same day.

05:51.699 --> 05:54.354
Then this dude
with the tats walks up.

05:54.397 --> 05:56.356
<i>♪</i>

05:56.399 --> 05:58.836
There's a hand-to-hand
exchange.

05:58.880 --> 06:00.403
So we ran him
through facial rec.

06:00.447 --> 06:01.883
It's Marco Perez.

06:01.926 --> 06:03.537
He is a shot caller
for the Latin Jokers.

06:03.580 --> 06:05.277
- This Perez,
he's got a long sheet,

06:05.321 --> 06:07.367
including an armed robbery
with a .45

06:07.410 --> 06:09.456
that was never recovered.

06:09.499 --> 06:11.066
Kevin's waiting
for his LKA.

06:11.109 --> 06:12.415
- He did three years
in Stateville

06:12.459 --> 06:13.851
on a distribution charge.

06:13.895 --> 06:17.028
The arresting officer on
that pinch was Mike Blaine.

06:17.072 --> 06:20.554
- So we got Blaine, on-duty,
receiving a suspicious envelope

06:20.597 --> 06:22.730
from a known banger
that he arrested.

06:22.773 --> 06:25.428
Two days later, he's shot
with a .45 while he's off-duty.

06:25.472 --> 06:26.951
None of this looks good.

06:26.995 --> 06:28.649
- Doesn't matter.
[phone chimes]

06:28.692 --> 06:31.086
We follow the leads
wherever they take us.

06:31.129 --> 06:32.870
- According to narcotics,
they're taking us

06:32.914 --> 06:35.264
to 2321 Holden Street.
He's got a stash house

06:35.307 --> 06:36.352
in Little Village.

06:36.396 --> 06:39.442
- Okay, good.
Let's roll.

06:41.705 --> 06:43.228
All right, listen.

06:43.272 --> 06:45.405
Until we know more,
I wanna keep this video

06:45.448 --> 06:47.581
of Blain and Perez off-book.

06:47.624 --> 06:50.105
- You got it, Sarge.

06:50.148 --> 06:57.112
<i>♪</i>

06:59.288 --> 07:00.594
- Jay, you set?

07:00.637 --> 07:02.552
- In position,
ready when you are.

07:02.596 --> 07:05.990
- Copy that.
We're moving in.

07:06.034 --> 07:08.993
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

07:09.037 --> 07:15.957
<i>♪</i>

07:20.918 --> 07:23.921
- Clear.
I'll take the right.

07:23.965 --> 07:30.885
<i>♪</i>

07:33.627 --> 07:37.282
<i>[distant gunfire]</i>

07:37.326 --> 07:40.982
<i>[muffled shouting]</i>

07:41.025 --> 07:46.466
<i>♪</i>

07:46.509 --> 07:49.164
<i>[gunfire grows louder]</i>

07:53.168 --> 07:54.517
- We got a runner!

07:54.561 --> 07:56.693
- Don't do it, Marco!
- Hands up!

07:56.737 --> 07:59.304
- You know the drill!
Show me, now!

07:59.348 --> 08:01.132
- Hands up!
- Hands up.

08:01.176 --> 08:02.438
- Get your ass down.

08:02.482 --> 08:05.136
- Stand up.
Walk back towards me.

08:05.180 --> 08:07.922
- Back just real slow.

08:08.836 --> 08:11.882
- Well, business must be good.

08:11.926 --> 08:15.146
Recovered 20 grand
at your stash.

08:15.190 --> 08:17.192
- I don't know what
you're talking about, bro.

08:17.235 --> 08:18.715
- Uh-huh.

08:18.759 --> 08:23.154
We found your gun, too.
Sig Sauer .45.

08:23.198 --> 08:26.593
Slugs are a match to a gun
used in a cop murder.

08:26.636 --> 08:28.943
- That's a lie.

08:28.986 --> 08:32.555
- Two days ago.
That's you.

08:32.599 --> 08:35.427
Talking to the dead cop.

08:35.471 --> 08:38.518
Mm-hmm.

08:38.561 --> 08:40.955
- I didn't kill Mike!

08:40.998 --> 08:44.088
I was in Gary last night.
I had my gun with me, too.

08:44.132 --> 08:46.351
- But you knew Mike Blaine?
- Yeah.

08:46.395 --> 08:48.484
He busted me four years ago.

08:48.528 --> 08:50.878
After I got out, we crossed
paths from time to time.

08:50.921 --> 08:53.533
Said hello, that sort of thing.
Became friends, kind of.

08:53.576 --> 08:55.230
- When's the last time
you saw him?

08:57.232 --> 08:59.321
- That day.

09:00.975 --> 09:03.499
- Tell me what's in
that envelope.

09:03.543 --> 09:05.545
- Money.

09:05.588 --> 09:07.503
Three grand.

09:07.547 --> 09:09.505
He needed a loan,
so I took care of him.

09:09.549 --> 09:11.289
Gave him a good deal, too.

09:11.333 --> 09:13.596
- Mike tell you
what he needed the money for?

09:13.640 --> 09:16.643
- No, just said
he needed it quick

09:16.686 --> 09:18.732
to help out a friend.

09:20.560 --> 09:22.170
- Anything else?

09:22.213 --> 09:23.388
- He was driving away...

09:23.432 --> 09:25.086
Some white boy
pulled up, though.

09:25.129 --> 09:27.088
Started taking
pictures with his phone.

09:27.131 --> 09:29.438
- Okay.
- Mike lost it.

09:29.481 --> 09:30.918
Started screaming at him.

09:30.961 --> 09:33.007
This white boy just
flipped him off and drove away.

09:33.050 --> 09:34.356
- You think he knew this kid?

09:34.399 --> 09:36.967
- I don't know, man,
it looked that way.

09:37.011 --> 09:41.450
- You get a good look at him?
- White, brown hair, 20s.

09:41.493 --> 09:43.147
Drove one
of those electric cars,

09:43.191 --> 09:46.281
like a Prius or something.

09:48.500 --> 09:50.154
That's all I know.

09:50.198 --> 09:53.027
<i>♪</i>

09:57.248 --> 09:59.773
- Hey, Sarge.
Perez's alibi checks out.

09:59.816 --> 10:01.035
There's video of him
at a gas station in Gary.

10:01.078 --> 10:02.471
Same time Blaine was shot.

10:02.514 --> 10:04.473
- So we eliminated Perez,
but take a look at this.

10:04.516 --> 10:07.215
We dug into his story about
the angry kid in the Prius.

10:07.258 --> 10:09.739
Led us to this guy,
Zach Phillips.

10:09.783 --> 10:10.958
- I found traffic cams

10:11.001 --> 10:12.437
four blocks away
from the crime scene.

10:12.481 --> 10:14.657
Silver Prius registered
to that same Zach Phillips.

10:14.701 --> 10:15.789
11:19 p.m.

10:15.832 --> 10:17.312
That's the same night
Blaine was shot.

10:17.355 --> 10:19.531
- On top of that, he filed
an excessive force complaint

10:19.575 --> 10:20.968
against Blaine
a few weeks back.

10:21.011 --> 10:22.230
- We showed Perez
a six-pack.

10:22.273 --> 10:24.319
He confirmed Zach
is the guy taking photos.

10:24.362 --> 10:26.321
- Okay, so what do we
know about Zach?

10:26.364 --> 10:28.540
- He's 25 years old.
He owns a graphic design firm.

10:28.584 --> 10:29.890
No priors.

10:29.933 --> 10:31.805
His only blemish is
a disorderly conduct pinch

10:31.848 --> 10:33.154
at a recent protest,

10:33.197 --> 10:34.764
where Blaine was
the arresting officer.

10:34.808 --> 10:36.374
- Two days after that bust,

10:36.418 --> 10:38.072
Zach started posting
on an anti-police website.

10:38.115 --> 10:39.726
Goes by the name FTPNow.

10:39.769 --> 10:41.684
We got him saying,
"Copaganda must end.

10:41.728 --> 10:43.207
"If CPD won't punish
Officer Blaine,

10:43.251 --> 10:44.556
"perhaps someone else will.

10:44.600 --> 10:46.471
Remember, Mike,
karma's a bitch."

10:46.515 --> 10:48.299
- [scoffs]

10:48.343 --> 10:49.953
And this is three days ago?

10:49.997 --> 10:51.433
- Mm-hmm.
- All right, split up.

10:51.476 --> 10:55.306
Check all possibilities.
Track him down now.

10:55.350 --> 10:58.266
<i>[tense music]</i>

10:58.309 --> 11:03.575
<i>♪</i>

11:03.619 --> 11:06.578
- He's in apartment 3G.
- Yeah, I just don't know if...

11:06.622 --> 11:08.885
- Yeah, okay.
- Zach Phillips?

11:08.929 --> 11:11.279
- Yeah?
What's going on?

11:11.322 --> 11:12.759
- Chicago PD.
We need to talk to you.

11:12.802 --> 11:14.586
- Ma'am, can you give us
a few minutes, please?

11:14.630 --> 11:17.198
- It's okay, babe.
I'll call you later.

11:18.721 --> 11:20.723
What's going on?
What is this?

11:20.767 --> 11:22.725
- It's about the murder
of a Chicago police officer.

11:22.769 --> 11:24.422
We need you to come down
to the district,

11:24.466 --> 11:25.380
help us clear up a few things.

11:25.423 --> 11:26.686
- Am I under arrest?

11:26.729 --> 11:27.817
- We wanna talk to you
about Mike Blaine--

11:27.861 --> 11:29.036
- I said, am I under arrest?

11:29.079 --> 11:30.080
- She just told you,
we need to--

11:30.124 --> 11:31.691
- I don't have to go anywhere.

11:31.734 --> 11:33.040
I know my rights.

11:33.083 --> 11:34.606
- Okay, now you're
under arrest.

11:34.650 --> 11:36.217
- Put your hands out
to the side.

11:36.260 --> 11:37.653
- Since you know so much,
you probably know that

11:37.697 --> 11:39.655
your latest post about
Mike Blaine is in violation

11:39.699 --> 11:42.440
of Section 20-12-9
of the Illinois Criminal Code--

11:42.484 --> 11:44.094
- That's aggravated assault.

11:44.138 --> 11:45.487
- You have the right
to remain silent.

11:45.530 --> 11:47.358
Anything you say or do can
and will be used

11:47.402 --> 11:48.620
against you in a court of law.

11:48.664 --> 11:50.666
You have the right
to an attorney.

11:50.710 --> 11:54.626
♪

11:54.670 --> 11:58.587
Where were you last night
around 11:00 p.m.?

11:58.630 --> 12:01.198
- On my way
to my girlfriend's apartment.

12:01.242 --> 12:03.244
- Does she live
on 109th Street?

12:03.287 --> 12:05.289
- No.
- Hmm.

12:05.333 --> 12:07.814
Were you driving on
109th Street at that time?

12:09.685 --> 12:11.382
- Um...possibly.

12:16.300 --> 12:18.912
- Let me refresh your memory,
Zach.

12:18.955 --> 12:23.046
That's you, caught on
a traffic cam at 11:19 p.m.

12:23.090 --> 12:24.613
on 109th Street.

12:24.656 --> 12:27.094
That's four blocks from
where Officer Blaine was shot.

12:27.137 --> 12:29.400
- Guessing I wasn't the only
one on the road at that time.

12:29.444 --> 12:30.880
- No, you weren't.

12:30.924 --> 12:34.536
But you were the only person
on the road at that time

12:34.579 --> 12:36.625
who filed an official complaint
against Officer Blaine,

12:36.668 --> 12:38.583
who made online threats
against Officer Blaine.

12:38.627 --> 12:41.630
- He practically broke
my kneecap with his nightstick.

12:41.673 --> 12:43.501
Then the bastard
handcuffed me

12:43.545 --> 12:45.068
and put me into the back
of a police car

12:45.112 --> 12:46.635
for three hours.

12:46.678 --> 12:49.812
<i>I told him I had asthma.
He didn't care.</i>

12:49.856 --> 12:50.987
Left me there to die.

12:51.031 --> 12:52.206
- You threw a rock
at him, Zach.

12:52.249 --> 12:54.295
- I didn't throw a damn thing.

12:54.338 --> 12:55.687
I swear to God.

12:55.731 --> 12:57.472
He thought I did,
so he stopped me

12:57.515 --> 12:58.734
and started bullying me.

12:58.778 --> 13:00.562
- So that's why you shot him,
for revenge?

13:00.605 --> 13:03.652
- No, I didn't shoot anyone.

13:03.695 --> 13:05.349
- Okay.

13:05.393 --> 13:08.178
So what were you doing
on 109th Street?

13:08.222 --> 13:09.789
<i>♪</i>

13:09.832 --> 13:12.008
- All right, Zach's apartment
was pretty clean.

13:12.052 --> 13:13.488
I gotta show you something.

13:13.531 --> 13:15.316
He had pictures
that he took of Blaine

13:15.359 --> 13:16.708
the night before the murder.

13:16.752 --> 13:17.927
He was definitely following him
and stalking him...

13:17.971 --> 13:19.799
- That doesn't mean
he killed Mike.

13:19.842 --> 13:21.365
I mean, this kid seems more
like a choir boy

13:21.409 --> 13:23.063
than a cop killer.

13:23.106 --> 13:25.543
- Either way,
he dug up some dirt.

13:25.587 --> 13:28.982
Digital footprint puts Blaine
at South Bishop Street

13:29.025 --> 13:30.810
at 9:00 p.m.
Now I know you know

13:30.853 --> 13:32.986
it's a high crime area--
drugs, hookers...

13:33.029 --> 13:37.512
Blaine waits by his car.
An unknown woman approaches.

13:37.555 --> 13:40.123
They share a quick hello.

13:40.167 --> 13:42.125
He then slips her
an envelope--

13:42.169 --> 13:43.561
I'm guessing it's the envelope

13:43.605 --> 13:45.520
he got from Perez
with the three grand in it.

13:45.563 --> 13:48.436
She proceeds to get
into his car.

13:48.479 --> 13:52.614
They stay there for ten
minutes...before she exits.

13:52.657 --> 13:54.398
Don't know what
happened inside,

13:54.442 --> 13:56.618
but obviously,
that doesn't look great.

13:56.661 --> 13:58.489
- Were you able to ID
the woman?

13:58.533 --> 14:01.579
- No, it's just...it's not
enough for facial rec.

14:01.623 --> 14:04.147
- Blaine got any CIs
that match her description?

14:04.191 --> 14:06.976
- No.

14:07.020 --> 14:09.457
So I'm guessing--
- Well, you don't get to guess,

14:09.500 --> 14:12.677
not on this one.

14:12.721 --> 14:15.245
Show the photos to his partner.
Maybe he can help.

14:15.289 --> 14:16.856
- All right.

14:16.899 --> 14:19.902
You got it, boss.

14:19.946 --> 14:22.165
- [sighs]

14:22.209 --> 14:24.689
- Sarge.

14:24.733 --> 14:28.128
- Hank,
you got a visitor.

14:28.171 --> 14:35.048
<i>♪</i>

14:35.962 --> 14:39.139
- [sighs]

14:39.182 --> 14:41.271
- Dana.
- Hank.

14:41.315 --> 14:43.839
- You okay?
- No.

14:43.883 --> 14:45.754
I'm trying to keep it
together, but...

14:45.797 --> 14:48.148
I'm getting the runaround
from Mike's district.

14:48.191 --> 14:51.455
I'm hearing that because
Mike might've been off-book,

14:51.499 --> 14:53.718
that the city won't pay
a full pension

14:53.762 --> 14:55.590
for a line-of duty death.
- Look, it's gonna be okay.

14:55.633 --> 14:58.071
I'm gonna look into it.
I'll see what's going on.

14:58.114 --> 14:59.942
- My kids need to know
that their dad died a hero.

14:59.986 --> 15:01.901
I know it doesn't sound
like much, but--

15:01.944 --> 15:03.728
- Hey, I understand.

15:03.772 --> 15:07.297
- And we need the benefits,
Hank.

15:07.341 --> 15:09.125
We're low on cash.
Real low.

15:09.169 --> 15:12.041
- Hey...

15:12.085 --> 15:14.609
I'm gonna take care of it.

15:14.652 --> 15:16.959
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

15:17.003 --> 15:19.701
Come on.

15:19.744 --> 15:22.443
- Hey, Smith--
- Hey, take her home.

15:22.486 --> 15:24.706
- Sure.

15:24.749 --> 15:28.884
- Mike was a good man,
and a good cop.

15:28.928 --> 15:31.713
- I know he was.

15:37.762 --> 15:41.853
- You should know, IAD is
looking into Blaine's murder.

15:41.897 --> 15:45.031
Rather than send him off
with a salute and a pension,

15:45.074 --> 15:47.555
they wanna catch him dirty.

15:51.472 --> 15:54.562
- Thanks, Trudy.

15:54.605 --> 15:56.346
Did you open
an IAD investigation

15:56.390 --> 15:57.304
into Mike Blaine?

15:57.347 --> 15:59.959
- I did.

16:00.002 --> 16:01.873
- This how we treat
dead cops now?

16:01.917 --> 16:03.788
Open an IAD investigation?

16:03.832 --> 16:05.660
What, we gotta make sure
they're squeaky clean

16:05.703 --> 16:08.097
before we console the widow,
pay their benefits?

16:08.141 --> 16:09.707
- I was just doing my job.

16:09.751 --> 16:12.406
- Come on, what's going on?
What am I missing?

16:14.756 --> 16:16.453
- The press is all over this.
I'm getting a lot of heat

16:16.497 --> 16:19.456
from FOP to give
a "slain hero" speech.

16:19.500 --> 16:21.893
But before I do that,
I need to know who he was.

16:21.937 --> 16:23.373
And who he wasn't.

16:23.417 --> 16:26.724
<i>♪</i>

16:26.768 --> 16:28.422
- Then you should
probably hold off

16:28.465 --> 16:32.121
on giving that hero speech
for now.

16:32.165 --> 16:34.297
We still can't explain
some of his movements.

16:34.341 --> 16:37.605
So just...let me
do a little more digging

16:37.648 --> 16:41.087
before you put
yourself out there.

16:41.130 --> 16:48.094
<i>♪</i>

16:54.013 --> 16:56.058
- [sighs]

16:56.102 --> 16:57.712
So what's the word
with your dad?

16:57.755 --> 17:00.454
- Uh...yeah, he's okay.

17:00.497 --> 17:02.195
Um...

17:02.238 --> 17:04.110
He's got two clogged arteries,

17:04.153 --> 17:06.155
so they need to do
a bypass surgery.

17:06.199 --> 17:08.984
- When?
- Two days.

17:09.028 --> 17:10.942
- What, are you
gonna go see him?

17:10.986 --> 17:14.729
- Yeah, maybe tomorrow.

17:14.772 --> 17:17.471
- Hailey--

17:17.514 --> 17:21.605
Look, I know who your dad was,
and I know what he did.

17:21.649 --> 17:25.087
But if something happens...
and you don't go see him,

17:25.131 --> 17:27.176
then you're gonna carry this
for the rest of your life.

17:27.220 --> 17:31.746
So don't do it for him,
just do it for you.

17:31.789 --> 17:33.269
- What do we know
about the woman

17:33.313 --> 17:35.576
in the photo with Blaine?
- Not a damn thing.

17:35.619 --> 17:37.882
Rodriguez didn't recognize her,
so I've gotta keep digging.

17:37.926 --> 17:39.145
- I got an email
from forensics--

17:39.188 --> 17:41.625
they said the mud
on Zach's tires is a match

17:41.669 --> 17:43.062
to the mud and rocks
at the crime scene.

17:43.105 --> 17:44.846
- Okay, great,
so Zach was there.

17:44.889 --> 17:47.457
But we got no evidence that
he actually did the murder.

17:47.501 --> 17:49.242
- I checked surveillance cams
in the area,

17:49.285 --> 17:50.678
came up with nothing.

17:50.721 --> 17:52.854
- I mean, do we really think
this dude did this?

17:52.897 --> 17:54.203
Two in the back?

17:54.247 --> 17:56.031
That's pretty hardcore
for a graphic designer.

17:56.075 --> 17:57.815
- We know he was there,

17:57.859 --> 18:00.818
and he's still
our only suspect.

18:00.862 --> 18:02.951
- All right, so let's go back,

18:02.994 --> 18:04.866
try talking to Zach
one more time.

18:04.909 --> 18:08.087
Just...play nice.

18:08.130 --> 18:10.654
Let's see if we can get
this kid to open up.

18:21.535 --> 18:24.799
- All right, Zach.
- [clears throat]

18:24.842 --> 18:27.410
- The evidence is piling up.

18:27.454 --> 18:29.630
The mud and rocks on your tires
are an exact match

18:29.673 --> 18:31.240
to the mud and rocks
at the crime scene.

18:31.284 --> 18:34.243
So we know you were there.

18:34.287 --> 18:35.853
We also know that
you've been following Blaine,

18:35.897 --> 18:37.812
taking pictures.

18:37.855 --> 18:40.467
- You're right, I was.

18:40.510 --> 18:43.992
I wanted to prove that he was
a bad person, a bad cop.

18:44.035 --> 18:46.864
Because I know you guys--
the Chicago Police Department--

18:46.908 --> 18:48.562
would never look into him,

18:48.605 --> 18:50.433
investigate the misconduct
report that I filed.

18:50.477 --> 18:52.348
- Well, it's not
a perfect system.

18:52.392 --> 18:54.220
You know, we get hundreds
of complaints every month.

18:54.263 --> 18:57.310
It takes time
to sort this stuff out.

18:57.353 --> 18:59.703
But I do understand how
that level of frustration

18:59.747 --> 19:01.705
could lead to a confrontation.

19:01.749 --> 19:03.185
- What are you saying?

19:03.229 --> 19:05.318
- I'm saying maybe
you confronted Blaine.

19:05.361 --> 19:08.321
You wanted to get some things
off your chest.

19:08.364 --> 19:09.800
Maybe he didn't like
what you had to say

19:09.844 --> 19:10.975
so he got aggressive.

19:11.019 --> 19:13.239
Maybe he reached for his gun.

19:13.282 --> 19:15.066
You just did what you had to do
because you were afraid

19:15.110 --> 19:17.243
he might cause you
serious bodily harm.

19:17.286 --> 19:18.418
That would be self-defense.

19:18.461 --> 19:19.810
You wouldn't be responsible
for his death.

19:19.854 --> 19:21.160
- Nice try.

19:21.203 --> 19:24.250
But that's not what happened.
- Zach...

19:24.293 --> 19:27.644
Right now,
you're our only suspect.

19:27.688 --> 19:29.559
This would be your opportunity
to prove us wrong.

19:29.603 --> 19:31.735
- I did not kill
Officer Blaine.

19:31.779 --> 19:33.650
I'll take a polygraph.

19:33.694 --> 19:36.087
Swear on a Bible,
my mother's grave.

19:36.131 --> 19:38.089
You name it, I'll do it.

19:44.400 --> 19:46.881
- Was Blaine with this woman
the night of the murder?

19:46.924 --> 19:50.101
- I'm not doing this.
Sorry.

19:50.145 --> 19:51.451
- If you're not the guy
that killed him,

19:51.494 --> 19:52.843
why not help us
find the person that did?

19:52.887 --> 19:54.410
- Because I'm not a hypocrite.

19:54.454 --> 19:56.195
- What the hell are you
talking about?

19:56.238 --> 19:57.848
- I don't like the police.
Never have.

19:57.892 --> 20:00.111
And that was before
Officer Blaine attacked me,

20:00.155 --> 20:01.461
wrongfully imprisoned me,

20:01.504 --> 20:02.984
and none of you did
anything about it.

20:03.027 --> 20:04.507
- He thought that
you threw a rock at him.

20:04.551 --> 20:07.467
- But I didn't!
- Okay, so he made a mistake.

20:07.510 --> 20:09.643
Just like every other
human being on this planet.

20:09.686 --> 20:11.862
So can we rise above
this petty anger?

20:11.906 --> 20:14.169
Maybe see the bigger picture?
- Why would I want to do that?

20:14.213 --> 20:15.518
- 'cause that's
what good people do.

20:15.562 --> 20:17.651
They realize
that people are flawed.

20:17.694 --> 20:19.522
They do stupid things,
sometimes.

20:19.566 --> 20:21.872
- What he did to me
was not just stupid.

20:21.916 --> 20:23.396
It was an abuse of power

20:23.439 --> 20:26.616
and a violation
of my civil rights.

20:26.660 --> 20:33.580
<i>♪</i>

20:41.283 --> 20:44.286
- This guy is unbelievable.

20:44.330 --> 20:47.463
<i>♪</i>

20:47.507 --> 20:48.508
What?

20:48.551 --> 20:49.857
- Your speech.

20:49.900 --> 20:51.598
"Good people know
that people are flawed,

20:51.641 --> 20:55.558
that they do
stupid things sometimes"?

20:55.602 --> 20:57.256
- Hailey, I wasn't
talking about you.

20:57.299 --> 20:59.475
I was talking about Zach.

20:59.519 --> 21:01.434
I know who your father is
and that he was abusive.

21:01.477 --> 21:04.132
- You don't know
the half of it.

21:04.175 --> 21:05.960
- No, you're right, I don't.
I'm sorry.

21:06.003 --> 21:08.441
You know I'm on your side.

21:08.484 --> 21:10.051
I'm just trying to help.
- I don't want your help.

21:10.094 --> 21:12.096
Not with this.

21:12.140 --> 21:17.232
<i>♪</i>

21:17.276 --> 21:18.755
- How'd it go with Zach?

21:18.799 --> 21:23.151
- He's not talking.

21:23.194 --> 21:24.805
- All right, take him home.

21:24.848 --> 21:31.464
<i>♪</i>

21:36.425 --> 21:37.774
- All right, Zach.

21:37.818 --> 21:39.733
You're officially released
from police custody.

21:39.776 --> 21:41.169
- Don't leave town.
We're probably gonna have

21:41.212 --> 21:42.518
some follow-up questions.

21:42.562 --> 21:44.085
- I told you,
I'm not cooperating.

21:44.128 --> 21:45.739
- Yeah, you made that
very clear.

21:48.263 --> 21:50.265
- Hey, there he is--
[indistinct chatter]

21:53.442 --> 21:55.531
- Zach, Zach--were you
questioned about the murder

21:55.575 --> 21:56.880
of Officer Mike Blaine?

21:56.924 --> 21:58.360
- Have you been charged
with a crime?

21:58.404 --> 22:00.231
<i>[phone buzzing]</i>

22:00.275 --> 22:03.017
- Oh, that's Platt.

22:03.060 --> 22:05.106
A witness just called in,
saw a car pull into an alley

22:05.149 --> 22:06.542
two blocks
from the crime scene.

22:06.586 --> 22:09.153
Driver ran in, and then,
30 seconds later, ran out.

22:09.197 --> 22:10.459
Witness'll meet us there.

22:10.503 --> 22:11.982
- Two blocks?
If we're lucky, that's

22:12.026 --> 22:13.593
our offender dumping a gun.
- Yeah, makes sense to me.

22:13.636 --> 22:16.378
- Let's go.

22:16.422 --> 22:19.033
- Anything?
- No gun.

22:19.076 --> 22:20.730
But it's disgusting.

22:24.865 --> 22:25.953
It's almost been an hour.

22:25.996 --> 22:27.650
Is this witness
ever gonna show up?

22:27.694 --> 22:29.739
- I don't know.
Maybe he got nervous.

22:29.783 --> 22:31.654
Or maybe someone told him
there's a new law

22:31.698 --> 22:34.091
that prohibits good people from
cooperating with the police.

22:34.135 --> 22:35.571
- Yeah, God forbid.

22:35.615 --> 22:37.051
Used to be, a cop got shot,
people'd come

22:37.094 --> 22:39.488
outta the woodwork to help.

22:42.752 --> 22:45.668
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

22:45.712 --> 22:48.889
- Gun!

22:48.932 --> 22:53.720
<i>♪</i>

22:53.763 --> 22:55.548
- Ballistics confirmed the gun
is the same gun

22:55.591 --> 22:57.463
used to murder Officer Blaine.

22:57.506 --> 22:58.855
They weren't able
to pull any prints,

22:58.899 --> 23:02.337
but they did trace the weapon
to a...Maria Guerra.

23:02.381 --> 23:04.252
Female Hispanic, 25, no priors.

23:04.295 --> 23:05.688
- She got any connection
to Zach Phillips?

23:05.732 --> 23:07.473
- No, none that I could find,
anyway.

23:07.516 --> 23:09.170
I also tracked down
that no-show witness.

23:09.213 --> 23:11.433
He's letting CPIC in now to
look at the security footage.

23:11.477 --> 23:13.435
- Yo, Sarge.
- Yeah?

23:13.479 --> 23:15.568
- Maria's the woman
in the photo with Blaine.

23:15.611 --> 23:17.396
- You got an address on her?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

23:17.439 --> 23:19.136
A two-flight in Pilsen,
moved out two months ago.

23:19.180 --> 23:22.052
Um...looks like she's been
off the radar ever since.

23:22.096 --> 23:24.446
- Let's track her down.

23:26.709 --> 23:29.712
- Cell phone GPS puts Maria
on this block.

23:29.756 --> 23:31.322
- All right, well,
we find her car,

23:31.366 --> 23:32.933
find where she's hiding.

23:32.976 --> 23:34.804
- Here.

23:34.848 --> 23:37.720
Blue Dodge.

23:37.764 --> 23:39.896
Plate matches.

23:39.940 --> 23:42.595
- Okay, I'm gonna hold down
the front

23:42.638 --> 23:44.771
just in case this ain't it.

23:44.814 --> 23:47.556
<i>♪</i>

23:47.600 --> 23:49.166
Yo, Sarge,
if you got ears,

23:49.210 --> 23:50.733
we got eyes on Maria's car.

23:50.777 --> 23:53.432
<i>- Copy that.
Keep me posted.</i>

23:56.565 --> 23:59.568
- Chicago PD!
Open up!

23:59.612 --> 24:01.875
- What's going on?
How can I help you?

24:01.918 --> 24:03.398
- We're looking
for Maria Guerra.

24:03.442 --> 24:05.487
- Um...

24:06.967 --> 24:09.709
Uh, she's--she's not here.
- You sure about that?

24:09.752 --> 24:11.972
We're investigating the murder
of a Chicago police officer.

24:12.015 --> 24:15.671
You wanna get wrapped
up in this?

24:15.715 --> 24:17.543
- Ruz!

24:17.586 --> 24:20.284
- Get back.
Step back.

24:20.328 --> 24:23.810
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:23.853 --> 24:28.075
<i>♪</i>

24:28.118 --> 24:30.947
- Maria?

24:33.123 --> 24:34.298
Hey, hey--

24:34.342 --> 24:36.518
Maria, come on.
Easy.

24:36.562 --> 24:38.694
Put that down.
Chicago PD.

24:38.738 --> 24:40.609
- Why are you here?
- To talk.

24:40.653 --> 24:42.306
But not if you got that knife
in your hand.

24:42.350 --> 24:44.308
You gotta put that down.
- No.

24:44.352 --> 24:48.269
- Nobody's gonna hurt you.
Okay?

24:48.312 --> 24:50.532
Put the knife down.

24:50.576 --> 24:52.752
Maria, put it down.
You wanna drop that.

24:52.795 --> 24:54.841
[quieter]
So put the knife down.

24:54.884 --> 24:57.844
All right?

24:57.887 --> 25:00.281
There you go.
[knife clatters]

25:00.324 --> 25:02.370
There you go.
Thank you.

25:04.241 --> 25:06.505
- What?
What are you doing?

25:06.548 --> 25:08.463
- Your gun was used to kill
Officer Mike Blaine.

25:08.507 --> 25:09.725
We just gotta take you
to the station--

25:09.769 --> 25:12.511
- You think--no,
I'd never hurt Mike!

25:12.554 --> 25:15.165
- Why's that?
- Because he saved my life.

25:15.209 --> 25:17.864
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

25:22.172 --> 25:24.523
- I told you,
I didn't kill Mike.

25:24.566 --> 25:26.829
- I get it, you liked him;
he saved your life.

25:26.873 --> 25:29.049
The problem is, Maria...

25:29.092 --> 25:31.573
the murder weapon
is registered in your name.

25:31.617 --> 25:34.576
- I know.

25:34.620 --> 25:37.710
But that's because...

25:37.753 --> 25:41.452
- That's because of what?

25:41.496 --> 25:44.020
- If I tell you,

25:44.064 --> 25:46.457
you need to protect
me and my family.

25:46.501 --> 25:48.938
- Protect you from who?

25:48.982 --> 25:51.941
- My ex-boyfriend.

25:51.985 --> 25:54.204
- Who's your ex-boyfriend?

25:57.338 --> 26:00.384
- [sniffs]
His name is Jose Torres.

26:02.082 --> 26:05.476
He took my gun,

26:05.520 --> 26:07.478
and used it to kill Mike.

26:07.522 --> 26:10.351
- Okay, why do you think
Jose killed Mike?

26:10.394 --> 26:12.527
<i>[somber music]</i>

26:12.571 --> 26:15.486
- Because Mike
was trying to help me.

26:15.530 --> 26:18.881
<i>♪</i>

26:18.925 --> 26:20.796
I broke up with Jose
about a month ago,

26:20.840 --> 26:23.625
but he was angry.

26:23.669 --> 26:28.064
He kept showing up at my house,
wanting to have sex.

26:28.108 --> 26:32.025
When I say no, he gets violent.

26:32.068 --> 26:34.418
So I finally called 911.

26:34.462 --> 26:37.030
- And that's when you met Mike?
- Yeah.

26:37.073 --> 26:40.555
Mike came to my house,
He talked to Jose...

26:40.599 --> 26:44.690
He had a bat in his hands,
but Mike talked him down.

26:44.733 --> 26:47.867
- Mike arrest Jose?
- No.

26:47.910 --> 26:50.347
- He put him in handcuffs,
but...

26:50.391 --> 26:52.175
I didn't want to press charges.

26:52.219 --> 26:54.308
I pleaded with Mike
not to arrest him.

26:59.879 --> 27:01.576
- I still don't understand

27:01.620 --> 27:03.709
why you think Jose
did the murder.

27:03.752 --> 27:07.190
<i>♪</i>

27:07.234 --> 27:11.673
- A few days ago...
Jose found me at my cousin's.

27:11.717 --> 27:15.372
I told him to get out,
but he went crazy,

27:15.416 --> 27:18.593
started punching walls
and breaking dishes.

27:18.637 --> 27:22.118
I was terrified,
so I pulled out my gun.

27:22.162 --> 27:26.383
I told him to leave, but he
took it out of my hands,

27:26.427 --> 27:30.213
started hitting me.
So I called Mike.

27:32.085 --> 27:34.304
- Is that the last time
you saw him?

27:34.348 --> 27:35.654
- Yeah.

27:35.697 --> 27:40.528
He showed up with some money,
three grand,

27:40.571 --> 27:43.400
told me to stay in a hotel
for a few weeks.

27:43.444 --> 27:45.925
He said he was
gonna talk to Jose,

27:45.968 --> 27:48.579
tell him to leave me alone.

27:50.930 --> 27:54.150
- Why didn't you
come to the police?

27:54.194 --> 27:56.457
- I was scared.

27:58.807 --> 28:02.245
Jose said that if I ever talked
to the police about him,

28:02.289 --> 28:06.728
that he was gonna kill
my daughter.

28:06.772 --> 28:10.471
I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

28:10.514 --> 28:13.082
That's not on you.

28:13.126 --> 28:15.606
It's on Jose.

28:15.650 --> 28:21.656
<i>♪</i>

28:21.700 --> 28:24.659
- Jose Torres.
- Maria's story checks out?

28:24.703 --> 28:26.052
- It seems legit.

28:26.095 --> 28:27.706
The 911 tape confirms
her call from last month,

28:27.749 --> 28:29.359
and a neighbor said he's heard
lots of fights over the years.

28:29.403 --> 28:30.752
- All right,
Torres got a sheet?

28:30.796 --> 28:31.927
- Yeah, he's got two DUIs

28:31.971 --> 28:33.102
and an assault
with a deadly weapon.

28:33.146 --> 28:34.669
It was a bar fight
that got out of hand.

28:34.713 --> 28:36.279
- Okay, what about
the night of the murder?

28:36.323 --> 28:37.803
- So the best lead that
we have right now is

28:37.846 --> 28:39.282
a hit on Torres's credit card.

28:39.326 --> 28:41.502
He was at a bar two blocks away
from the murder.

28:41.545 --> 28:43.547
He paid his tab at 10:45.
He must've met up with Blaine

28:43.591 --> 28:44.723
right after that.

28:44.766 --> 28:46.463
- I mean, we could put
Maria in play.

28:46.507 --> 28:47.987
Wire her up,
get her talking to Torres--

28:48.030 --> 28:49.292
- No, that's too dangerous.

28:49.336 --> 28:50.772
Can't put Maria and Torres
in the same room.

28:50.816 --> 28:53.296
- I agree.

28:53.340 --> 28:55.821
All right, we gotta find
another way to nail this prick.

28:55.864 --> 28:57.953
- What about Zach Phillips?

28:57.997 --> 28:59.172
He was there the night
of the murder.

28:59.215 --> 29:01.348
Maybe he saw Torres.
- Yeah, she's right.

29:01.391 --> 29:03.567
Give it a shot.
Let's go.

29:11.837 --> 29:13.752
- That's him pulling up.

29:22.456 --> 29:25.720
- Zach, we need to talk
to you one more time.

29:25.764 --> 29:27.200
- I'm not talking to you.

29:27.243 --> 29:28.810
- Look, we know you didn't kill
Mike Blaine.

29:28.854 --> 29:32.031
We just want you to look
at some photos, okay?

29:32.074 --> 29:33.423
Did you see any of these men

29:33.467 --> 29:34.642
the night you were
following him?

29:34.685 --> 29:38.124
- I told you,
I'm not getting involved.

29:38.167 --> 29:40.474
[tires squealing]

29:40.517 --> 29:43.999
- Get down!
[rapid gunfire]

29:44.043 --> 29:46.785
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

29:46.828 --> 29:50.919
<i>♪</i>

29:50.963 --> 29:52.834
- 5021 Georgia, got shots fired
at the police.

29:52.878 --> 29:54.793
It's a black Audi traveling
westbound on 19th street.

29:54.836 --> 29:57.056
Hailey, you good?
- Yeah.

29:57.099 --> 29:59.101
Are you okay?
- Yeah, yeah, he missed.

29:59.145 --> 30:02.104
[both panting]

30:02.148 --> 30:04.324
- You okay?
- Thank you.

30:04.367 --> 30:07.109
You saved my life.
Thank you.

30:17.032 --> 30:18.860
- Can we get you
something to drink?

30:18.904 --> 30:20.688
Coffee, water?
- No, thanks.

30:20.731 --> 30:22.516
- I'd offer you food,
but we don't have much.

30:22.559 --> 30:23.822
Maybe the odd candy bar--

30:23.865 --> 30:25.606
- I'm not hungry,
but thank you.

30:25.649 --> 30:27.042
- Okay.

30:27.086 --> 30:29.305
Well, now that you've had
some time to calm down--

30:29.349 --> 30:32.265
- I refuse to answer.

30:32.308 --> 30:34.876
- Okay.

30:34.920 --> 30:38.880
Zach, we believe the offender
saw you on the news,

30:38.924 --> 30:42.971
talking to reporters,
so he knows you were there,

30:43.015 --> 30:45.756
<i>that you saw him arguing
with Blaine,</i>

30:45.800 --> 30:48.324
maybe even shooting him.

30:48.368 --> 30:51.893
Okay, that makes you a witness.
It also makes you a target.

30:51.937 --> 30:53.460
He's not gonna stop
coming after you.

30:53.503 --> 30:55.157
- That's my problem.

30:55.201 --> 30:56.289
I'll move out of state

30:56.332 --> 30:57.812
until all this nonsense
blows over.

30:57.856 --> 30:59.683
- It's not nonsense,
and it's not gonna blow over,

30:59.727 --> 31:02.730
not without your help.

31:04.601 --> 31:06.647
- Zach,
she just saved your life.

31:11.260 --> 31:16.483
Without this woman, without
this evil cop right here...

31:16.526 --> 31:18.702
you'd be dead.

31:18.746 --> 31:20.226
You get that, right?

31:20.269 --> 31:23.098
- I do,
and I'm very appreciative.

31:23.142 --> 31:25.057
But that doesn't change--
- Yes, it does!

31:25.100 --> 31:26.885
It does.

31:26.928 --> 31:28.495
You need to quit hating.

31:28.538 --> 31:31.019
And if not for yourself,
then do it for Blaine's family,

31:31.063 --> 31:33.804
and help them get justice.
- Justice?

31:33.848 --> 31:36.590
W-we don't know what
he was doing with this guy.

31:36.633 --> 31:37.939
He could've been
dealing drugs--

31:37.983 --> 31:39.245
- We do know what he was doing!

31:39.288 --> 31:41.116
He was trying to save
a young woman's life,

31:41.160 --> 31:45.816
to stop this guy
from continuing to abuse her.

31:45.860 --> 31:48.167
That's what he was doing there.

31:48.210 --> 31:50.517
- That very well may
be true, but--

31:50.560 --> 31:52.649
- No, it is true!
That's a fact!

31:52.693 --> 31:55.565
<i>- And what he did to me
is a fact.</i>

31:55.609 --> 31:59.395
And if I choose to hate him
for that, that's up to me,

31:59.439 --> 32:01.093
not you.

32:01.136 --> 32:04.009
- Zach, let it go.
Just let it go.

32:06.968 --> 32:09.362
Accept the fact
that he made a mistake.

32:09.405 --> 32:13.018
- No, that was not a mistake.
That's who he was.

32:13.061 --> 32:15.890
I could see it in his eyes.

32:15.934 --> 32:18.632
He was a mean, violent man.

32:21.374 --> 32:23.419
What he did was unforgivable.

32:23.463 --> 32:26.422
<i>[somber music]</i>

32:26.466 --> 32:28.511
<i>♪</i>

32:28.555 --> 32:31.993
<i>- Okay, that's it.</i>

32:32.037 --> 32:34.604
- Sarge.
Patrol found the stolen Audi.

32:34.648 --> 32:36.084
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

32:36.128 --> 32:37.216
There's blood in it.
It's a match for Torres.

32:37.259 --> 32:38.782
- He got caught
in the crossfire?

32:38.826 --> 32:40.001
- It would make sense,
I mean,

32:40.045 --> 32:41.307
Jay said he got off
five or six rounds.

32:41.350 --> 32:42.786
- Good.
That puts him at the scene.

32:42.830 --> 32:43.874
We know where this guy is?

32:43.918 --> 32:45.267
- He's on the run right now.

32:45.311 --> 32:47.269
- All right, get a BOLO out
on him and his vehicle--

32:47.313 --> 32:49.010
- Already done.
It's a gold Dodge pickup.

32:49.054 --> 32:51.795
- 'Kay.
- We'll follow up.

32:51.839 --> 32:54.755
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:54.798 --> 32:59.455
<i>♪</i>

32:59.499 --> 33:02.850
- All right, this is the spot.

33:02.893 --> 33:05.200
Yeah, patrol got it right.
That's Torres's truck.

33:05.244 --> 33:07.376
Gold Dodge Ram.

33:07.420 --> 33:08.595
- Sarge, you got your ears on?

33:08.638 --> 33:10.336
<i>- Yeah, Hailey,
go with your traffic.</i>

33:10.379 --> 33:13.426
- Torres is here; he's parked
in a lot off Whipple and 26th.

33:13.469 --> 33:14.949
Right by the hot dog spot.

33:14.993 --> 33:16.472
<i>- All right, keep eyes
and an anchor down.</i>

33:16.516 --> 33:18.605
<i>Everybody on the air,
start heading that way.</i>

33:18.648 --> 33:19.998
- That's him.

33:20.041 --> 33:22.217
Sarge, Torres just stepped out.

33:22.261 --> 33:23.784
<i>- Take him.</i>

33:23.827 --> 33:25.133
<i>-</i> I'll block the entrance.
- Wait for my signal.

33:25.177 --> 33:26.743
I'm gonna cover the other side.
- All right.

33:26.787 --> 33:33.881
<i>♪</i>

33:38.929 --> 33:41.715
- [speaking indistinctly]

33:41.758 --> 33:44.326
Listen, I gotta go.

33:44.370 --> 33:51.290
<i>♪</i>

33:51.333 --> 33:53.857
- Damn it.

33:53.901 --> 33:57.209
Jay, I gotta move!

33:57.252 --> 33:59.820
[tires squeal]

33:59.863 --> 34:02.214
<i>♪</i>

34:02.257 --> 34:04.520
[honking]

34:04.564 --> 34:06.740
Chicago PD, get your hands up!

34:06.783 --> 34:09.656
Hands up!
Hey--

34:09.699 --> 34:11.005
- I'll shoot her.

34:11.049 --> 34:13.094
- Just take it easy, man.
No one's gotta get hurt.

34:13.138 --> 34:14.617
Just let her go.
- I'll shoot her.

34:14.661 --> 34:16.097
- Let me go, please!
- Take it easy, take it easy!

34:16.141 --> 34:18.534
Put the gun down.
Just let her go!

34:18.578 --> 34:20.536
- Get back in your car
and out of my way...

34:20.580 --> 34:22.103
- No!
- Or I'll kill her!

34:22.147 --> 34:23.626
Get back in your car!
- [screaming]

34:23.670 --> 34:26.107
- Drop the gun!
- I said get back in your car!

34:26.151 --> 34:28.109
- Torres--
- Or I'll shoot her!

34:28.153 --> 34:30.155
Get back!

34:30.198 --> 34:33.245
- [grunting]
- [screams]

34:33.288 --> 34:35.160
<i>♪</i>

34:35.203 --> 34:37.858
- Ma'am, are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

34:37.901 --> 34:39.381
- Jose Torres, you're under
arrest for the attempted murder

34:39.425 --> 34:40.469
of Zach Phillips,

34:40.513 --> 34:42.123
and for the murder

34:42.167 --> 34:44.343
of Chicago Police Officer
Mike Blaine.

34:44.386 --> 34:51.306
<i>♪</i>

34:52.786 --> 34:54.004
- I got some
really good news for you.

34:54.048 --> 34:55.354
- Yeah, I'll take it.

34:55.397 --> 34:57.312
- We got a hit
off a security cam near

34:57.356 --> 35:00.141
where Torres dumped the gun.
- Okay.

35:00.185 --> 35:02.665
- That's Torres right there,
holding the murder weapon

35:02.709 --> 35:04.145
two blocks away
from the crime scene

35:04.189 --> 35:06.191
three minutes
after the shooting.

35:06.234 --> 35:08.758
- That should seal it.
- Mm.

35:08.802 --> 35:10.282
Best movie I've seen
in a while.

35:10.325 --> 35:12.110
- All right, I'll talk to
state's attorney's office,

35:12.153 --> 35:13.807
get the paperwork going.
Nice work.

35:13.850 --> 35:15.809
- Um, boss, about the file.
- Hmm?

35:15.852 --> 35:19.508
- You remember we left
some stuff out?

35:19.552 --> 35:22.250
- I want everything you got,
good and bad.

35:22.294 --> 35:24.513
I'll take it from there.
- All right.

35:28.604 --> 35:31.868
- You've been saying
you wanted transparency.

35:31.912 --> 35:33.740
Well, this is me
being transparent.

35:33.783 --> 35:36.090
That's--that's
everything I got.

35:36.134 --> 35:37.657
- You loop in
the state's attorney's office?

35:37.700 --> 35:40.312
- Writing up charges as we
speak, first degree murder.

35:42.183 --> 35:45.230
The only thing left
to talk about

35:45.273 --> 35:47.232
is the legacy of Mike Blaine.

35:47.275 --> 35:49.190
- Yeah, well,
it doesn't look good.

35:49.234 --> 35:51.236
- I guess that depends
on your point of view.

35:51.279 --> 35:52.802
- Excuse me?

35:52.846 --> 35:54.326
- Sam, everything he did,

35:54.369 --> 35:56.980
he did to help protect
a victim of domestic abuse.

35:57.024 --> 35:59.505
- He borrowed $3,000
from a convicted felon,

35:59.548 --> 36:01.898
failed to report
the domestic abuse incident,

36:01.942 --> 36:04.292
and violated countless rules
and regulations.

36:04.336 --> 36:05.685
- Okay?

36:05.728 --> 36:08.078
What's your point?

36:08.122 --> 36:10.777
- Blaine was far from perfect.
- You're right.

36:10.820 --> 36:12.735
But he was a good man.

36:12.779 --> 36:14.302
He died trying to protect

36:14.346 --> 36:17.000
a scared, vulnerable
young mother.

36:17.044 --> 36:18.350
And how he did it?

36:18.393 --> 36:19.960
I mean, what rules
he chose to ignore?

36:20.003 --> 36:21.179
Who cares?

36:21.222 --> 36:23.050
He was trying to do
something good.

36:23.093 --> 36:25.400
That's what matters.

36:25.444 --> 36:28.098
You know, there was a time
we actually forgave people

36:28.142 --> 36:30.884
for their mistakes.

36:30.927 --> 36:36.019
We understood that
human beings are fallible.

36:36.063 --> 36:37.891
So you look at
the sum of the parts.

36:37.934 --> 36:41.677
Does the good outweigh
the bad?

36:41.721 --> 36:43.766
I mean, Mike Blaine--

36:43.810 --> 36:47.857
he gave his life
doing something good...

36:47.901 --> 36:50.382
brave...

36:52.384 --> 36:54.386
Noble.

36:54.429 --> 36:58.520
<i>♪</i>

36:58.564 --> 37:01.871
And that makes him a hero.

37:01.915 --> 37:09.052
<i>♪</i>

37:14.275 --> 37:16.538
- I don't have
to hide anymore?

37:16.582 --> 37:18.410
He's actually in jail?

37:18.453 --> 37:21.021
- Yeah, and he will be
for a long time.

37:21.064 --> 37:23.241
- You just have to testify.

37:23.284 --> 37:26.766
Tell the jury
that he took your gun.

37:26.809 --> 37:29.464
- Yes, I will.

37:29.508 --> 37:33.076
What he did to me...
I can't forget, but...

37:33.120 --> 37:35.862
knowing that he's out
of my life forever--

37:35.905 --> 37:38.517
that's good enough.

37:38.560 --> 37:40.736
Gives me what I need
to move on.

37:40.780 --> 37:43.826
<i>♪</i>

37:43.870 --> 37:46.394
- If you ever need anything...

37:46.438 --> 37:50.006
[phone chimes]
- Come on.

37:59.494 --> 38:02.541
- All good?

38:02.584 --> 38:06.153
- Yeah, they moved
my dad's surgery to tonight.

38:06.196 --> 38:08.068
- I'm not gonna tell you
what to do--

38:08.111 --> 38:10.984
- I'm going to the hospital
right now.

38:12.290 --> 38:14.292
I'll see you later?

38:18.644 --> 38:21.081
- Today, we apprehended the man
we believe murdered

38:21.124 --> 38:25.085
Officer Michael R. Blaine,
a 22-year veteran

38:25.128 --> 38:27.392
of the Chicago Police
Department.

38:27.435 --> 38:29.872
<i>Officer Blaine died
the same way</i>

38:29.916 --> 38:31.309
<i>he lived his life:</i>

38:31.352 --> 38:34.224
<i>trying to do what was right,</i>

38:34.268 --> 38:36.662
<i>trying to serve
this city with dignity.</i>

38:36.705 --> 38:38.359
<i>And like most of us,</i>

38:38.403 --> 38:40.796
<i>Officer Blaine
was not perfect.</i>

38:40.840 --> 38:43.364
<i>But when you look at the sum
of the parts...</i>

38:43.408 --> 38:46.324
<i>at the man in full,</i>

38:46.367 --> 38:48.978
<i>it's clear that the good
offset the bad,</i>

38:49.022 --> 38:52.808
<i>that he was a brave
and decent police officer</i>

38:52.852 --> 38:54.810
<i>who died on the job
trying to save</i>

38:54.854 --> 38:57.247
<i>a young woman,
who was tragically stuck</i>

38:57.291 --> 39:00.207
<i>in a violent
and abusive relationship.</i>

39:00.250 --> 39:04.429
<i>To me, that makes
Mike Blaine a hero.</i>

39:04.472 --> 39:07.301
<i>He represented
the best of what</i>

39:07.345 --> 39:10.522
<i>the Chicago Police Department
is all about.</i>

39:12.828 --> 39:14.787
<i>That being said,
it's important to acknowledge</i>

39:14.830 --> 39:17.616
<i>that we don't always
get it right.</i>

39:17.659 --> 39:22.925
<i>The Chicago Police Department
is not flawless.</i>

39:22.969 --> 39:25.537
<i>We've made some mistakes.</i>

39:25.580 --> 39:30.368
<i>We've committed
certain unforgivable acts.</i>

39:30.411 --> 39:33.022
<i>But those misdeeds,
no matter how egregious,</i>

39:33.066 --> 39:34.720
<i>should not define us,</i>

39:34.763 --> 39:38.245
but rather motivate us
to do better,

39:38.288 --> 39:40.508
to be more complete
and compassionate

39:40.552 --> 39:44.643
human beings
and police officers.

39:44.686 --> 39:51.389
<i>♪</i>

40:16.718 --> 40:18.590
[knocking]

40:25.118 --> 40:27.903
- Hi.
- Hey.

40:27.947 --> 40:30.863
- Beer?
- Yeah, sure.

40:32.821 --> 40:34.954
So how'd it go?

40:34.997 --> 40:38.566
- Uh...
[sighs]

40:38.610 --> 40:41.351
Good.

40:41.395 --> 40:43.876
Glad I talked to him.

40:59.239 --> 41:01.937
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

41:01.981 --> 41:09.162
<i>♪</i>

41:28.268 --> 41:31.401
[wolf howls]
